<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=J._R._R._Tolkien&amp;action=edit&amp;section=36" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h3>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-3" style="-moz-column-count:3; column-count:3;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> See J. R. R. Tolkien's own phonetic transcription published on the illustration in <i>The Return of the Shadow: The History of The Lord of the Rings, Part One.</i> [Edited by] Christopher Tolkien. London: Unwin Hyman, [25 August] 1988. (The History of Middle-earth; 6) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0044401620" class="internal">ISBN 0-04-440162-0</a>. The position of the stress is not entirely fixed: stress on the second syllable <i>(tol<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">kien</span></i> rather than <i><span style="font-variant:small-caps;">tol</span>kien)</i> has been used by some members of the Tolkien family.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Humphrey Carpenter, "Tolkien; The Authorised Biography," page 111, 200.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Middle-earth" is derived from an Anglicized form of Old Norse <a href="/wiki/Midgard" title="Midgard">Miðgarðr</a>, the land inhabited by humans in <a href="/wiki/Norse_mythology" title="Norse mythology">Norse mythology</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <i>Letters</i>, nos. 131, 153, 154, 163.</li>
<li id="cite_note-de_Camp-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-de_Camp_4-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFde_Camp1976"><a href="/wiki/L._Sprague_de_Camp" title="L. Sprague de Camp">de Camp, L. Sprague</a> (1976). <i><a href="/wiki/Literary_Swordsmen_and_Sorcerers" title="Literary Swordsmen and Sorcerers">Literary Swordsmen and Sorcerers: The Makers of Heroic Fantasy</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Arkham_House" title="Arkham House">Arkham House</a>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0870540769" class="internal">ISBN 0-87054-076-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%5B%5BLiterary+Swordsmen+and+Sorcerers%7CLiterary+Swordsmen+and+Sorcerers%3A+The+Makers+of+Heroic+Fantasy%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=de+Camp&amp;rft.aufirst=L.+Sprague&amp;rft.au=de+Camp%2C+L.+Sprague&amp;rft.date=1976&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BArkham+House%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-87054-076-9&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:J._R._R._Tolkien"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> The author emphasizes the impact of not only Tolkien but also of <a href="/wiki/William_Morris" title="William Morris">William Morris</a>, <a href="/wiki/George_MacDonald" title="George MacDonald">George MacDonald</a>, <a href="/wiki/Robert_E._Howard" title="Robert E. Howard">Robert E. Howard</a> and <a href="/wiki/Eric_R%C3%BCcker_Eddison" title="Eric Rücker Eddison">E. R. Eddison</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMitchell.2C_Christopher">Mitchell, Christopher. <a href="http://www.veritas.org/media/talks/585" class="external text" title="http://www.veritas.org/media/talks/585" rel="nofollow">"J. R. R. Tolkien: Father of Modern Fantasy Literature"</a>. Veritas Forum<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.veritas.org/media/talks/585" class="external free" title="http://www.veritas.org/media/talks/585" rel="nofollow">http://www.veritas.org/media/talks/585</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-03-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=J.+R.+R.+Tolkien%3A+Father+of+Modern+Fantasy+Literature&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mitchell%2C+Christopher&amp;rft.au=Mitchell%2C+Christopher&amp;rft.pub=Veritas+Forum&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.veritas.org%2Fmedia%2Ftalks%2F585&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:J._R._R._Tolkien"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
